<p><strong>Career Links</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>All Types / General Geoscience<br /></td>
<td>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.monster.com/" target="_blank">www.monster.com</a> - The best site for environmental &amp; petroleum jobs. Also includes some salary information. </li>
<li><a href="http://www.ajb.dni.us/" target="_blank">America's Job Bank</a> </li>
<li><a href="http://geology.com/" target="_blank">Geology and Earth Science Jobs</a> </li>
<li><a href="http://www.uni-mainz.de/FB/Geo/Geologie/jobs/index.html" target="_blank">Geoscience Jobs</a> </li>
<li><a href="http://www.earthworks-jobs.com/" target="_blank">Earth Science Jobs</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.careercornerstone.org/geosciences/geosci.htm" target="_blank">Sloan Career Cornerstone Center</a> - Gives guidance on geoscience careers and has links to job opportunities. </li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Academic<br /></td>
<td>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.academiccareers-jobs.com/" target="_blank">Academic Careers Online</a> </li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Petroleum <br /></td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Find links to petroleum-only sites in <a href="http://www.aapg.org/" target="_blank">www.aapg.org</a>. </li>
<li><a href="http://www.rigzone.com/" target="_blank">www.rigzone.com</a> - includes an extensive directory of petroleum and service companies </li>
</ul>
(Service companies provide data and services to petroleum companies. They generally hire people with 2-5 years of industry experience, and are excellent employers). 
<ul>
<li>Some petroleum companies: <a href="http://www.hess.com/" target="_blank">Amerada Hess</a>, <a href="http://www.anadarko.com/" target="_blank">Anadarko</a>, <a href="http://www.bp.com/" target="_blank">BP-Amoco-Arco</a>, <a href="http://www.chevron.com/" target="_blank">ChevronTexaco</a>, <a href="http://www.conocophillips.com/index.htm" target="_blank">ConocoPhillips</a>, <a href="http://www.exxonmobil.com/corporate/" target="_blank">ExxonMobil</a>, <a href="http://www.marathon.com/" target="_blank">Marathon</a>, <a href="http://www.pioneernrc.com/" target="_blank">Pioneer Resources</a>, <a href="http://www.byui.edu/geology/www.pioneernrc.com" target="_parent"></a><a href="http://www.saudiaramco.com/irj/portal/anonymous" target="_blank">Saudi Aramco</a>, <a href="http://www.shell.com/" target="_blank">Shell</a>, <a href="http://www.total.com/en/home_page/" target="_blank">TotalFinaElf</a>, and others. </li>
</ul>
A few of their web sites include job postings, and most discuss careers.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Environmental / Engineering<br /></td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>One of the largest, URS employs 25,000 in the environmental &amp; engineering fields. Includes job postings. See what this company does. <a href="http://www.enr.com/" target="_blank">www.enr.com</a> </li>
<li><a href="http://www.brookes.ac.uk/geology/geoljobs/eartjobs.html#general" target="_blank">Earth and Environmental Science Jobs</a> </li>
<li>Other environmental companies: <a href="http://www.bechtel.com/" target="_blank">Bechtel</a>, <a href="http://www.tetratech.com/portal/site/TetraTech/" target="_blank">Tetratech</a>, <a href="http://www.parsons.com/default.asp" target="_blank">Parsons</a>, <a href="http://www.ch2m.com/corporate/" target="_blank">CH2Mhill</a>, <a href="http://www.golder.com/" target="_blank">Golder Associates</a>, <a href="http://www.westonsolutions.com/" target="_blank">Weston Solutions</a>, <a href="http://www.earthtech.com/" target="_blank">EarthTech</a>, <a href="http://www.shawgrp.com/" target="_blank">Shaw Group</a>, <a href="http://www.brownandcaldwell.com/" target="_blank">Brown and Caldwell</a>, <a href="http://www.jacobs.com/" target="_blank">Jacobs</a>, <a href="http://www.wgint.com/" target="_blank">Washington Group</a> , and others.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.engineering-job-site.com/" target="_blank">Engineering Jobs</a> </li>
</ul>
(Advice: Privately-owned companies tend to treat employees a little better than publicly traded ones).</td>
